How to live stream MLB games in 2024

No matter your allegiance, we know you want to live stream your favorite MLB team during the 2024 season. To safely and securely enjoy baseball with ExpressVPN, just follow these easy steps:

Get ExpressVPN.

Connect to a server location that matches the broadcaster you want to watch. For example, fans living anywhere from the United Kingdom and France to Hong Kong and Japan can tune into MLB.TV International to watch their favorite teams.

Head to your preferred streaming platform, such as MLB.TV or YouTube TV.

Tune in to the action!

Some users watch MLB games by connecting to a VPN server in a country other than their own, but doing so may violate copyright or the streaming service’s terms of use. ExpressVPN is a privacy and security tool, and using it to circumvent copyright is against our Terms of Service. We cannot see or control what you do while connected to our VPN, so you are responsible for ensuring that your use complies with all relevant terms and laws.

Live stream MLB games on MLB.TV

The easiest way to watch every MLB game is with an MLB.TV subscription. MLB.TV is available globally, and ExpressVPN works seamlessly with MLB.TV to ensure you can stream the action privately and securely.

MLB.TV

Price: 30 USD/month or 150 USD/season

The MLB.TV app is the most comprehensive and affordable option for streaming the entire MLB season. MLB.TV International users can live stream the Home Run Derby, All-Star Game, and postseason without blackouts. MLB.TV also offers a multiview feature, allowing subscribers to watch up to four games at once on supported Apple TV, Fire TV and Google TV devices. The service comes with a seven-day free trial, and also offers a monthly option.

Please note that blackouts still apply to MLB.TV users in the United States, Canada, and Guam.

MLB blackout policy explained

Unfortunately for baseball fans, “blackout” does not refer to a team and its fans wearing dark uniforms. Blackout instead refers to games being unavailable to stream in certain regions because the regional sports networks (RSNs) own the distribution rights. For example, a Yankees fan living in New York City cannot watch Aaron Judge and the Bronx Bombers on MLB.TV because the YES Network (the Yankees’ RSN) distributes the rights to cable companies (and select cord-cutting services) in the area.

The blackout policy also applies to fans living in states without MLB teams, such as Iowa or New Hampshire. Blackouts are sometimes determined by ZIP codes. Although New Jersey lacks Major League Baseball, those with a northern New Jersey ZIP code (such as 07006) cannot watch the Yankees or Mets on MLB.TV. However, those with a ZIP code in southern New Jersey (i.e., 08002) can watch Yankees and Mets games, though they cannot stream the Philadelphia Phillies.

Additionally, the Toronto Blue Jays‘ blackout policy covers all of Canada. The Boston Red Sox (the Maritimes), Minnesota Twins (Saskatchewan and Manitoba), and Seattle Mariners (British Columbia and Alberta) are also blacked out in select Canadian provinces. All San Francisco Giants and Oakland Athletics live games are unavailable in the U.S. territory of Guam.

MLB.TV’s blackout policy extends to select regular-season games (including any airing on ESPN), the All-Star Game, and all postseason games for U.S. customers. However, a customer who owns MLB.TV International is not subject to blackouts.

Please note blackouts do not apply to audio-only feeds. That Yankees fan living in Manhattan? Although they can’t watch the game, they can stream the audio on their phone, computer, Fire TV, or whatever device they choose—so long as MLB.TV is supported on said device, of course!

Arizona Diamondbacks, Colorado Rockies, and San Diego Padres blackouts explained

Beginning in 2023, Major League Baseball began directly offering fans in select regions (originally Arizona and San Diego) the ability to watch in-market Diamondbacks and Padres games through MLB.TV amid issues with their regional sports networks. Previously, a D–backs fan living in Phoenix could not stream a Diamondbacks game on MLB.TV, regardless of what channel it aired on. However, that is no longer the case, and team-specific packages are available for those in local markets.

As of 2024, the in-market MLB.TV package applies only to Diamondbacks, Padres, and Colorado Rockies fans. (The team-specific packages for those living out-of-market, such as a Rockies fan living in Baltimore or a Diamondbacks fan now residing in Atlanta, remain available!)

Diamondbacks, Padres, and Rockies fans are still subject to the blackout rule featuring select regular-season games, the All-Star Game, and the playoffs.

2024 MLB.TV U.S. and International Blackout Schedule

Baseball fans can find a list of blacked-out games on Major League Baseball’s official website.

Where to watch MLB games with free trials

Fubo

Price: 80 USD/month and up

Channels: ESPN, ESPN 2, Fox, FS1, MLB Network, select regional sports networks

Country: U.S.

On the downside, Fubo does not offer TBS, which airs national games on Tuesdays and select postseason games. However, fans from the United States can watch baseball games airing on Turner channels through Fubo if you purchase Max and the Bleacher Report Sports Add-On tier for Max, each of which cost 10 USD/month.

Fubo remains one of the few cord-cutting services to offer select regional sports networks for U.S. viewers, such as Marquee Sports Network (Cubs), NBC Sports Bay Area (Giants), NESN (Red Sox), and Root Sports Northwest (Mariners). Note that for games on regional sports networks, the teams available to you will be determined by the home zip code on your billing account. In addition, the “Sports Plus” package that includes MLB Network costs an additional 11 USD per month. Fubo also announced that it will include MLB.TV as an add-on for 25 USD/month, though standard blackout rules still apply. Fubo comes with a 7-day free trial.

Note: You will need a U.S. credit/debit card to subscribe. The billing address used may determine which local channels are available, and you may be unable to change your location.

DirecTV Stream

Price: 85 USD/month and up

Channels: ESPN, ESPN 2, Fox, FS1, FS2, MLB Network, TBS, select regional sports networks

DirecTV Stream is often on the pricier side, especially if you want the MLB Network, but it’s a great option for U.S. fans to stream MLB games if you prefer a cord-cutting service over an additional streaming app. The service offers a 5-day free trial.

YouTube TV

Price: 73 USD/month and up

Channels: ESPN, ESPN 2, Fox, FS1, FS2, TBS

YouTube TV offers Americans a variety of channels that carry MLB games, and the subscription costs 73 USD/month. You may need to submit a U.S. ZIP code (e.g., 10022, 48104, etc.), but it accepts a wide array of payment options. If you don’t feel like committing to YouTube TV, use the free trial. However, note that YouTube TV no longer carries MLB Network following a carriage dispute in 2023.

Want it on the big screen? Learn about all the ways to get ExpressVPN on your TV.

Amazon Prime Video

Price: 25 USD/month for the MLB.TV add-on

Amazon Prime offers MLB.TV as an add-on for 25 USD/month (on top of the regular 139 USD annual membership). Yankees fans can also watch select games on Amazon Prime Video. There’s a 30-day free trial available.

Apple TV+

Price: 14 USD/month (seven-day free trial)

MLB games are back on AppleTV+ for the 2024 season! You can catch Friday Night Baseball throughout the year on Apple TV+. Although the games are no longer free, AppleTV+ does offer a 7-day free trial you can take advantage of. Although blackouts do not apply, please note that the games will exclusively air on Apple TV+. However, you can still listen to the radio feed via the MLB app.

Other ways to watch MLB games in 2024

United States

Sling TV

Price: Varies

Channels: ESPN, ESPN 2, Fox, FS1, FS2, TBS, select regional sports networks

Sling TV includes channels that carry MLB games, such as ESPN, MLB Network, TBS, Fox, and FS1, as well as some regional sports networks. To get all of these channels, American subscribers need to get Sling Orange as well as Sling Blue. Use the “Sports Extra” add-on for Sling TV in order to watch MLB Network for an extra 10 USD/month. Please note that Sling no longer offers a free trial as of 2024.

Hulu+Live TV

Price: 77 USD/month

Channels: ESPN, ESPN 2, Fox, FS1, FS2, MLB Network, TBS, select regional sports networks

Hulu+Live TV offers most of the national channels broadcasting MLB for American fans. Select regional sports networks are also available. A free trial is not available.

Canada

TSN

Price: 20 CAD/month

Canadian baseball fans can live stream Toronto Blue Jays games, as well as select MLB games, on TSN+. While it doesn’t offer a free trial, TSN+ does allow users to purchase a one-day pass for less than 11 CAD (which is handy if you only want to watch a specific game).

Note: You may need a Canadian payment method to subscribe.

United Kingdom

Sky Sports

Price: 22 GBP/month and up

Channels: Sky Sports

Living in the UK? Sky Sports is your best bet for catching live streams of the games. You will also need to provide a valid postal code and a UK/Ireland credit or debit card.

If you have a Sky subscription, you can stream content with Sky Go by connecting to a secure server location in the UK and then logging in to your Sky Go account.

When will the 2024 MLB season start?

The 2024 MLB season officially begins Wednesday, March 20, when the Los Angeles Dodgers and San Diego Padres meet in Seoul, South Korea. The traditional Opening Day is Thursday, March 28.
